<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksum&auml;&auml;r </eesti>
<inglise>Tax rate </inglise>
<eesti>Sotsiaalmaksu m&auml;&auml;r on 33 protsenti maksustatavalt summalt. </eesti>
<inglise>The rate of social tax is 33 per cent of the taxable amount. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksustamisperiood </eesti>
<inglise>Taxable period </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Sotsiaalmaksuga maksustamise periood on kalendrikuu, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud juhul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The taxable period for social tax is one calendar month, except in the case provided for in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) F&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku ettev&otilde;tlusest saadud tulu sotsiaalmaksuga maksustamise periood on kalendriaasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The taxable period for social tax on income received from enterprise by a natural person is one calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksu laekumine </eesti>
<inglise>Receipt of tax </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksuamet kannab k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvi 10 l&otilde;ike 1 punktide 4 ja 5 alusel sotsiaalmaksu erikontole laekunud sotsiaalmaksu &uuml;le &uuml;he pangap&auml;eva jooksul riikliku pensionikindlustuse eelarvesse ja riikliku ravikindlustuse eelarvesse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Pursuant to clauses 10 (1) 4) and 5) of this Act, the Tax Board shall transfer social tax received in the special social tax account into the state pension insurance budget and the state health insurance budget within one banking day. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riikliku pensionikindlustuse eelarvesse &uuml;lekantava sotsiaalmaksu osa m&auml;&auml;r on 20 protsenti ja riikliku ravikindlustuse eelarvesse &uuml;lekantava sotsiaalmaksu osa m&auml;&auml;r on 13 protsenti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The proportion of social tax transferred into the state pension insurance budget is 20 per cent and the proportion of social tax transferred into the state health insurance budget is 13 per cent. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Sotsiaalmaksu maksmise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for payment of social tax </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvides 4 ja 6 s&auml;testatud sotsiaalmaksu maksja on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Payers of social tax provided for in &sect;&sect; 4 and 6 of this Act are required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) arvestama k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvi 2 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1-7 ja 9 s&auml;testatud sotsiaalmaksuga maksustatavatelt summadelt sotsiaalmaksu iga kindlustatava kohta ja maksma k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 7 toodud m&auml;&auml;ras sotsiaalmaksu, arvestades k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktis 2 s&auml;testatut; </eesti>
<inglise>1) calculate social tax for every insurable person on amounts provided for in clauses 2 (1) 1) - 7) and 9) of this Act which are subject to social tax, and pay social tax at the rate specified in &sect; 7 of this Act, having regard to the provisions of clause 2) of this subsection; </inglise>
<eesti>(15.06.98 j&otilde;ust.16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 61, 982) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.06.98 entered into force 16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 61, 982) </inglise>
<eesti>2) maksma t&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tulepingu alusel f&uuml;&uuml;silisele isikule makstud tasult sotsiaalmaksu, kui t&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tulepingus ei ole m&auml;rgitud, et t&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja on ettev&otilde;tlusega tegelev f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik ja ta on end oma elukohaj&auml;rgses Maksuameti kohalikus asutuses sellise isikuna registreerinud; </eesti>
<inglise>2) pay social tax on remuneration paid to natural persons on the basis of a contract for services unless stated in the contract for services that the contractor is a natural person engaged in enterprise and the natural person is registered in the local Tax Board Office of his or her residence as such; </inglise>
<eesti>3) maksma erisoodustustelt sotsiaalmaksu, isikustamata neid summasid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) pay social tax on fringe benefits, without reference to each insurable person separately; </inglise>
<eesti>4) &uuml;le kandma tasumisele kuuluva sotsiaalmaksu Maksuameti pangakontole maksustamisperioodile j&auml;rgneva kuu k&uuml;mnendaks kuup&auml;evaks ja esitama samaks kuup&auml;evaks elu- v&otilde;i asukohaj&auml;rgsele Maksuameti kohalikule asutusele vastava maksudeklaratsiooni; </eesti>
<inglise>4) transfer the social tax due to the bank account of the Tax Board by the tenth day of the month following the taxable period and submit the corresponding tax return to the local Tax Board Office of the residence or seat of the payers of social tax by the same date; </inglise>
<eesti>(18.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 29, 397; 15.09.99 j&otilde;ust.09.10.99 - RT I 1999, 71, 685; 15.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 101, 903) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 29, 397; 15.09.99 entered into force 09.10.99 - RT I 1999, 71, 685; 15.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 101, 903) </inglise>
<eesti>5) arvutama igakuiselt iga kindlustatava kohta k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 6 l&otilde;ike 1 alusel makstava sotsiaalmaksu ja selle &uuml;le kandma j&auml;rgneva kuu k&uuml;mnendaks kuup&auml;evaks Maksuameti pangakontole ning esitama samaks kuup&auml;evaks asukohaj&auml;rgsele Maksuameti kohalikule asutusele vastava maksudeklaratsiooni; </eesti>
<inglise>5) calculate the social tax payable pursuant to subsection 6 (1) of this Act for every insurable person each month, and transfer it to the bank account of the Tax Board by the tenth day of the following month and submit the corresponding tax return to the local Tax Board Office of the seat of the payer of social tax by the same date; </inglise>
<eesti>(18.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 29, 397; 15.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 101, 903) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 29, 397; 15.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 101, 903) </inglise>
<eesti>6) andma isikule, kellele maksti sotsiaalmaksuga maksustatavaid summasid v&otilde;i kelle eest maksti sotsiaalmaksu k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvi 6 l&otilde;ike 1 alusel, t&otilde;endi nendelt arvestatud ja makstud sotsiaalmaksu kohta isiku n&otilde;udmisel ja kalendriaastale j&auml;rgneva aasta 1. veebruariks. </eesti>
<inglise>6) issue to a person to whom amounts which are subject to social tax have been paid or for whom social tax has been paid pursuant to subsection 6 (1) of this Act a certificate concerning the amount of social tax calculated and paid for such person, at the request of the person, by 1 February of the year following the given calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>Isiku t&ouml;&ouml;lt lahkumisel antakse eelnimetatud t&otilde;end koos l&otilde;pparvega, pensioni taotlemiseks aga isiku n&otilde;udmisel. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon a person leaving employment, the aforementioned certificate shall be issued together with the final settlement; for the purposes of applying for pension, such certificate shall be issued at the request of the person. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ettev&otilde;tlusega tegelev f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A natural person engaged in enterprise is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) maksma maksustamisperioodi kestel sotsiaalmaksu avansiliste maksetena kvartalile j&auml;rgneva kuu 25. kuup&auml;evaks iga kuu eest v&auml;hemalt eelarveaastaks riigieelarvega kehtestatud kuum&auml;&auml;ralt arvutatud summas, v&auml;lja arvatud isik, kes on samaaegselt riikliku pensioni saaja ja k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud juhul; </eesti>
<inglise>1) pay social tax for each month during the taxable period as advance payments by the twenty-fifth day of the month following the end of a quarter at least in the amount calculated on the basis of the monthly rate established by the state budget for the budgetary year, except a person who concurrently receives a state pension, or in the case provided for in subsection (3) of this section; </inglise>
<eesti>(18.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 29, 397; 24.10.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 84, 536) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 29, 397; 24.10.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 84, 536) </inglise>
<eesti>2) esitama elukohaj&auml;rgsele Maksuameti kohalikule asutusele sotsiaalmaksu aastadeklaratsiooni hiljemalt maksustamisperioodile j&auml;rgneva aasta 31. m&auml;rtsiks ja tasuma k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 4 punktis 1 nimetatud juurdemaksmisele kuuluva maksusumma 1. juuliks Maksuameti pangakontole. </eesti>
<inglise>2) submit an annual social tax return to the local Tax Board Office of his or her residence by no later than 31 March of the year following the taxable period, and pay the additional amount of tax due specified in clause (4) 1) of this section to the bank account of the Tax Board by 1 July. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 29, 397) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 29, 397) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui ettev&otilde;tlusega tegeleva f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku eest maksab sotsiaalmaksu ka t&ouml;&ouml;andja, v&otilde;ib tema ettev&otilde;tlusest saadud tulult iga kuu eest makstavate avansiliste maksete summa olla eelarveaastaks riigieelarvega kehtestatud kuum&auml;&auml;ralt arvutatud maksusummast v&auml;iksem, kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt tema eest ja tema ettev&otilde;tlusest saadud tulult avansiliste maksetena makstav sotsiaalmaksu summa kuu kohta kokku on v&auml;hemalt v&otilde;rdne eelarveaastaks riigieelarvega kehtestatud kuum&auml;&auml;ralt arvutatud maksusummaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If social tax for a natural person engaged in enterprise is also paid by an employer, the amount of monthly advance payments payable on his or her income received from enterprise may be less than the amount of tax calculated on the basis of the monthly rate established by the state budget for the budgetary year, if the total monthly amount of social tax payable as advance payments for him or her by the employer and of social tax payable on his or her income received from enterprise is at least equal to the amount of tax calculated on the basis of the monthly rate established by the state budget for the budgetary year. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 29, 397; 24.10.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 84, 536) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 29, 397; 24.10.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 84, 536) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Maksuamet on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Tax Board is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teatama ettev&otilde;tlusega tegelevale f&uuml;&uuml;silisele isikule kirjalikult v&auml;hemalt 30 p&auml;eva enne maksu tasumise t&auml;htp&auml;eva tema poolt sotsiaalmaksu aastadeklaratsioonis esitatud andmete alusel juurdemaksmisele kuuluva maksusumma; </eesti>
<inglise>1) notify a natural person engaged in enterprise in writing, at least thirty days prior to the due date for payment of tax, of the additional amount of tax due on the basis of the information submitted in the annual social tax return by the natural person; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tagastama, v&auml;lja arvatud maksukorralduse seaduse (RT I 1994, 1, 5; 2000, 45, 279) paragrahvi 10 l&otilde;igetes 3 ja 4 s&auml;testatud juhtudel, ettev&otilde;tlusega tegelevale f&uuml;&uuml;silisele isikule enammakstud sotsiaalmaksu summa tema sotsiaalmaksu aastadeklaratsioonis v&otilde;i eraldi esitatud taotluse alusel maksustamisperioodile j&auml;rgneva aasta 1. juuliks. </eesti>
<inglise>2) refund overpaid amounts of social tax to a natural person engaged in enterprise on the basis of an application contained within his or her annual social tax return or submitted separately, by 1 July of the year following the taxable period, except in the cases provided for in subsections 10 (3) and (4) of the Taxation Act (RT I 1994, 1, 5; 2000, 45, 279). </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Maksudeklaratsioonide vormid ja t&auml;itmise korra ning maksu arvestamise korra kehtestab rahandusminister koosk&otilde;lastatult sotsiaalministriga. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The standard format and procedures for completion of tax returns and the procedure for calculation of tax shall be established by the Minister of Finance in concordance with the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(5 (1)) Asutuse t&ouml;&ouml;tajate, kelle koosseis, koondandmed v&otilde;i konkreetsed t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesanded on riigisaladus, sotsiaalmaksu arvestust peetakse rahandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(5 (1)) The social tax of employees of such agencies whose staff, consolidated data or specific duties constitute a state secret shall be calculated pursuant to the procedure established by a regulation of the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 101, 903) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 101, 903) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Iga kindlustatava kohta arvutatud sotsiaalmaksu summa &uuml;mardatakse t&auml;iskroonideks - summat alla 50 sendi ei arvestata ning 50 senti ja &uuml;le selle &uuml;mardatakse kroonini. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The amount of social tax calculated for each insurable person shall be rounded to full kroons - the amount less than 50 cents is not taken into account and the amount exceeding 50 cents shall be rounded to the next full kroon. </inglise>
